#PREAMBLE - installing Git
0. https://git-scm.com/download/mac
1. Validate install -> open Terminal type "git"

#Install Visual Studio Code
https://code.visualstudio.com/download
0. once it's installed open it, hover over icons, click on Extensions and install "Vim" for vi functionality when using Visual Studio Code.
#GIT setup HOWTO
0. login to github in your browser, create a repo called "KB"
1.clone the git repo from your gitbash cli:
git clone https://github.com/mpkdelphix/KB.git
2. check status
git status
3. add changed README.md
git add README.md
4. Now we do our first commit 
git commit -m "Primero!"
5. Now we attempt to push our changed README.md back to github, this will open dialog boxes in your browser for username
and your password - Git only accepts personal access tokens: Git->Settings->DeveloperSettings->Personal Access Token.
CLick the X to close username dialogbox and enter your git user name at command line; Then click the X to close the dialog box for your Git password and enter your persoonal access token at the command-line; You are now fully authenticated
git branch
git push origin main
git status
git log


